                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d817">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War 1939/1238: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-13T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >January 13, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>329. It is not quite clear from your 163, January 7, 7 p.m. whether you intended
                    to suggest that the Department should broach this subject <pb facs="1280"
                        n="1266" xml:id="pg_1266"/> to the Soviet Government.<note n="6"
                        xml:id="d817fn6">In telegram 349, January 14, 4 p.m., the Ambassador replied
                        that telegram 163 was forwarded simply for information (740.00116 European
                        War 1939/1750).</note> In any event the Department doubts the wisdom of its
                    taking any action at this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
